cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video summarization, which is a task related to visual understanding. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper introduces a new dilated temporal relation (DTR) unit, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of a discriminator to enforce information completeness and compactness, which could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
